problem.markdown:
>> In RNNs, the gradient can vanish or explode because a weight matrix is multiplied by itself many times in the gradient computation process.|| Select true or false. <<

(x) True {{This is a problem that RNN's face. The exploding gradient problem can be fixed with a small adjustment such as gradient clipping, but the vanishing gradient problem is harder to address.}}
( ) False {{ The vanishing gradient problem happens when a weight matrix with small values is multiplied by itself many times in the gradient computation process. The exploding gradient problem occurs when a weight matrix with large values is multiplied by itself many times in the gradient computation process. Since RNNs use the same weight matrices at every time step, they can encounter these problems.}}
